  "chapter": {
    "number": 1,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Beginning of Knowledge"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "These are the proverbs of Solomon son of David,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "king of Israel,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "for gaining wisdom and discipline,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for comprehending words of insight,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "and for receiving instruction in wise living",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and in righteousness, justice, and equity.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "To impart prudence to the simple",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4187
          },
          {
            "text": "and knowledge and discretion to the young,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "let the wise listen and gain instruction,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the discerning acquire wise counsel",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "by understanding the proverbs and parables,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the sayings and riddles of the wise.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The fear of the LORD is the beginning of knowledge,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but fools",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4188
          },
          {
            "text": "despise wisdom and discipline.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Enticement of Sin"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Listen, my son, to your father’s instruction,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and do not forsake the teaching of your mother.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For they are a garland of grace on your head",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a pendant around your neck.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My son, if sinners entice you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "do not yield to them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If they say, “Come along, let us lie in wait for blood,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "let us ambush the innocent without cause,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "let us swallow them alive like Sheol,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and whole like those descending into the Pit.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "We will find all manner of precious goods;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "we will fill our houses with plunder.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Throw in your lot with us;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "let us all share one purse”—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "my son, do not walk the road with them",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or set foot upon their path.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For their feet run to evil,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and they are swift to shed blood.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "How futile it is to spread the net",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "where any bird can see it!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But they lie in wait for their own blood;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they ambush their own lives.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Such is the fate of all who are greedy,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "whose unjust gain takes the lives of its possessors.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Wisdom Calls Aloud"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Wisdom calls out in the street,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "she lifts her voice in the square;",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "in the main concourse",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4189
          },
          {
            "text": "she cries aloud,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "at the city gates she makes her speech:",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“How long, O simple ones, will you love your simple ways?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "How long will scoffers delight in their scorn",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and fools hate knowledge?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If you had repented at my rebuke,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "then surely I would have poured out my spirit on you;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I would have made my words known to you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Because you refused my call,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and no one took my outstretched hand,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "because you neglected all my counsel,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and wanted none of my correction,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "in turn I will mock your calamity;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will sneer when terror strikes you,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "when your dread comes like a storm,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your destruction like a whirlwind,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "when distress and anguish overwhelm you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then they will call on me, but I will not answer;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will earnestly seek me, but will not find me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For they hated knowledge",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and chose not to fear the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 30,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They accepted none of my counsel;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they despised all my reproof.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 31,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So they will eat the fruit of their own way,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and be filled with their own devices.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 32,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the waywardness of the simple will slay them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the complacency of fools will destroy them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 33,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But whoever listens to me will dwell in safety,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "secure from the fear of evil.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 4187,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "The Hebrew word rendered simple in Proverbs refers to one who is naive, without moral direction, or inclined to evil.",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 4
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 4188,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "The Hebrew words rendered as fool in Proverbs denote one who is morally deficient.",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 7
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 4189,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or from the top of the wall",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 21
        }
      }
    ]
